node.js

Some short scripts for node.js tracing.  These require the node DTrace provider,
and a working version of the translator (/usr/lib/dtrace/node.d).

You should also check out:

- Robert Mustacchi's post on the node.js DTrace provider:
  http://dtrace.org/blogs/rm/2011/03/01/dtrace-probes-for-node-v0-4-x/

- Dave Pacheco's nhttpsnoop
  https://github.com/davepacheco/nhttpsnoop

- Dave Pacheco's post on profiling node.js stack traces using DTrace (with my
  flame graphs :)
  http://dtrace.org/blogs/dap/2012/04/25/profiling-node-js/

- Bryan Cantrill's Velocity talk on node.js and DTrace
  http://www.slideshare.net/bcantrill/instrumenting-the-realtime-web-nodejs-in-production
